This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with ranking images based on their relevance. Additionally, it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it involves analyzing and ordering images. The use of supervised learning suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The mention of datasets and applications suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of sub-sequences and structural ranking information suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
